<p>BYU-Idaho currently provides a browser-based web editing tool called the <a href="http://webtools.byui.edu/">Web Editor</a>.  This tool was developed by BYU-Idaho and is the preferred method for  web development. Pages and sites created using the Web Editor are  supported by the web services team located with University  Communications.</p>
<br />
<p><strong>Get in the Web Editor </strong></p>
<p><a href="http://www.byui.edu/WebDev/createapage.htm">Help and tips on creating a Web page</a>, as well as access to the Web Editor can be found at the <a href="http://webtools.byui.edu/">webtools page</a>.  Contact Bob Reed to get your user name in the Web Editor for a current  site or to set up a new site. You will need your BYU-I login name, and  the name of the organization or department.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Bob Reed</strong></p>
<p>(208) 496-2149</p>
<p>reedr@byui.edu</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>What is the Web Editor? </strong></p>
<p>The <a href="http://webtools.byui.edu/">Web Editor</a> is a  browser based editor that allows the user to create and edit Web pages  within their department or section. This means no software has to be  installed on your computer, and you will have access to the templates  used across campus.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Templates </strong></p>
Web page templates give the BYU-Idaho website a  consistent structure and appearance. This creates a standard throughout  the website which increases ease of navigation and overall usability of  the site.
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
